Tips： 
• Owner permission: Owner owns the account, manages account permissions, manages Active and other roles;
 • Active permissions: Active has other permissions such as transfer, voting, etc.
• Weight threshold: The weight threshold is the minimum weight requirement for using permission;
• Weight: The weight standard of public key. The higher the number, the higher the weight;
• Permission change should starts from small to large, such as Active first and then Owner;
• When changing permissions, please ensure that the new public key or account name is accurate;
• Before changing permissions, please make sure the assets has been properly managed.
